<div class="balanced-diet-section">
	<div class="deliver-image">
		<%= image_tag "http://res.cloudinary.com/depgwjsnd/image/upload/v1495492841/d_l7m1y5.jpg", class: "deliver-image" %>
	</div>
	<div class="icon-large icon-deliver text-center">
		<h4>BALANCED DIET</h4>
		<p>Fat is essential to human wellbeing, it provides energy and makes you feel full. Our bodies require both saturated and unsaturated fats in order to absorb vitamins A, D, E and K.  We make sure to include both fats in your meals: saturated fat, mostly found in animal foods and unsaturated, mostly found in plant foods. The amount of fat in your diet will be calculated and reflected in your food boxes. 
		<br></br> 
		As for our carbohydrates, most of meals contain complex carbohydrates. These do an excellent job of keeping you full and are less fattening because they take longer for our bodies to metabolise them. Most of the carbohydrates in our menus derive from plenty of seeds, green and root vegetables, pseudocereals and grains. This is turn creates dishes which better regulate  your blood sugar levels. </p>
	</div>
</div>
