			<h6>FISH</h6>
			<p>Fish and seafood is also important in our meal plans, we choose sustainable stock, which are wild and ethically caught.  As well as being a good source of protein, fish, particularly oily varieties contain high levels of Vitamin D which most people are deficient in. 
		</p>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="nutrition-box">
		<%= image_tag "http://res.cloudinary.com/depgwjsnd/image/upload/v1495478869/Rectangle_4_qgj1bg.jpg", class: "nutrition-image" %>
		<div class="nutrition-text">
			<h6>DAIRY</h6>
			<p>We use minimal dairy products, choosing nut and coconut milks, oat cream and coconut yoghurt as delicious alternatives. In cases where we do use dairy, we will label this in our box and we can guarantee it will always be full-fat from organic pasture-reared animals.</p>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="nutrition-box">
		<%= image_tag "http://res.cloudinary.com/depgwjsnd/image/upload/v1495478869/Rectangle_2_gbkygt.png", class: "nutrition-image" %>
		<div class="nutrition-text">
			<h6>FLAVOURINGS</h6>
			<p>Herbs and spices are the key to vibrant and delectable dishes; we pick most of our herbs from our own garden in Hertfordshire and use fresh spices where possible. When using oil for cooking, coconut is our preference as it has a multitude of health benefits. However, our kitchen is also stocked with nut, seed and olive oils for use in our favourite dressings and sauces. 
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
<div class="nutrition-images-bottom">
	<div class="nutrition-box">
		<%= image_tag "http://res.cloudinary.com/depgwjsnd/image/upload/v1495487357/Screen_Shot_2017-05-22_at_19.28.40_jfgbn9.jpg", class: "nutrition-image" %>
		<div class="nutrition-text">
			<h6>GRAINS, PSEUDOCEREALS, NUTS, SEEDS AND LEGUMES</h6>
			<p>The only grains we use in our meals are black, brown and red rice. Other than that we focus on pseudocereals; buckwheat, amaranth and quinoa. These are free from gluten and rich in amino acids.  You will see nuts and seed scattered all over our menus and we like to use legumes as a source of added protein.
			<br></br> 
			All grains, pseudocereals, nuts, seeds and legumes have a natural, protective layer called phytic acid – an anti nutrient that irritates the gut. Although a small amount of phytic acid is healthy, we activate these ingredients by soaking them. This starts the germination process and reduces the amount of phytic acid, which makes their nutrients easier to absorb and digest by your body. 
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="nutrition-box">
		<%= image_tag "http://res.cloudinary.com/depgwjsnd/image/upload/v1495487357/Screen_Shot_2017-05-22_at_19.28.4_bnhozj.jpg", class: "nutrition-image" %>
		<div class="nutrition-text">
			<h6>FRUIT AND VEGETABLES</h6>
			<p>FRUITS AND VEGETABLES
			Fruit and more notably vegetables make up so much of our menus. Vegetables are full of nutrients and are incredibly alkalizing which helps our bodies to function at their best. <br></br>
			We make sure to provide your body with a rainbow of vegetables and fruits, which keeps meals interesting and balanced. We also aim to buy seasonally to ensure you are getting the very best produce. When we have a glut of fruits or vegetables we put them through our HAKUNA fermentation or pickling process. Fermented (or cultured) foods are essential to good health, enhancing immune function and improving digestion. Our homemade cultured vegetables provide your body with a concentrated form of natural probiotics. </p>
		</div>
	</div>
